{{Infobox college football player |name=Dick Abernathy |image=dickabernathy.jpg |caption= |image_size=200px |birth_date= |birth_place= |death_date= |death_place= |height_ft=6 |height_in=2 |weight_lb=203 |currentposition=[[End (American football)|End]] |school=Vanderbilt Commodores |class=Graduate |pastschools=[[Vanderbilt Commodores football|Vanderbilt]] (1927&ndash;1929) |highlights= *[[College Football All-Southern Team|All-Southern]] ([[1928 College Football All-Southern Team|1928]], [[1929 College Football All-Southern Team|1929]]) *[[All-America]]n ([[1928 College Football All-America Team|1928]]) }} '''Richard "Dick" Abernathy''' was a [[college football]] player.
==Vanderbilt University== Abernathy was a prominent [[End (American football)|end]] for [[Dan McGugin]]'s [[Vanderbilt Commodores football|Vanderbilt Commodores]] of [[Vanderbilt University]] from [[1927 Vanderbilt Commodores football team|1927]] and [[1929 Vanderbilt Commodores football team|1929]].
===1928=== In [[1928 Vanderbilt Commodores football team|1928]], Abernathy began the season with two touchdown catches against Chattanooga in a 20–0 win.<ref name=king/> He also caught a 38–yard touchdown pass that helped Vanderbilt defeat Colgate 12–7.<ref name=dick>{{cite web|url=http://www.vucommodores.com/sports/m-footbl/all-americans-abernathy.html|title=Dick Abernathy}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2206&dat=19281007&id=ItktAAAAIBAJ&sjid=O9gFAAAAIBAJ&pg=3218,4596886|title=Vanderbilt Defeats Colgate Under Burning Sun|work=The Miami News|date=October 7, 1928}}</ref> In Dallas, Abernathy blocked a punt that was recovered in the end zone. The resulting touchdown gave the Commodores' a 13–12 win over Texas.<ref name=king>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RS4VAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA123|title=Where Football Is King: A History of the SEC|author=Christopher J. Walsh|page=123}}</ref><ref name=dick/> At year's end he was selected [[College Football All-America Team|All-America]]n.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ten Schools Picked On All-American Team By Popular Vote|work=The Davenport Democrat And Leader|date=1928-12-09}}</ref>
==Chautauqua== Abernathy advertised Redpath [[Chautauqua]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/1978043//|date=May 8, 1930|accessdate=March 13, 2015|page=10|title=Football Star Is Advertising Show|work=Kingsport Times|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}} {{Open access}}</ref>
