'''Peter Fuchs''' (28 October 1955 &ndash; 22 September 1980) was a British [[Alpine skiing|alpine skier]]. He competed in [[Alpine skiing at the 1976 Winter Olympics|three events]] at the [[1976 Winter Olympics]].<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fu/peter-fuchs-1.html |title=Peter Fuchs Olympic Results |accessdate=17 March 2018}}</ref> He was killed in a car accident.<ref name="death">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2000/dec/30/books.guardianreview |title=The white stuff |work=The Guardian |accessdate=17 March 2018}}</ref>

