{{Infobox book| <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = The Future of the Mind: The Scientific Quest to Understand, Enhance, and Empower the Mind | image = The Future of the Mind bookcover.jpg | caption = Hardcover edition | author = [[Michio Kaku]] | cover_artist = | awards = No.1 New York Times Bestseller | country = United States | language = English | genre = [[Popular science]] | publisher = [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]] | release_date = February 25, 2014 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]]) | pages = 400 pp. | isbn = 978-0385530828 | dewey = | congress = | oclc= | preceded_by = [[Physics of the Future]] | followed_by = }}
'''''The Future of the Mind: The Scientific Quest to Understand, Enhance, and Empower the Mind''''' is a [[popular science]] book by the [[futurist]] and [[physicist]] [[Michio Kaku]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/09/books/review/michio-kakus-future-of-the-mind.html?_r=0|publisher=New York Times|title=Dreaming in Code: Michio Kaku’s ‘Future of the Mind’|accessdate=23 June 2014}}</ref> The book was initially published on February 25, 2014 by [[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Future-Mind-Scientific-Understand-Enhance/dp/038553082X/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&ie=UTF8&qid=1417028247&sr=1-1&keywords=The+Future+of+the+Mind&pebp=1417024647376|publisher=[[amazon.com]]|title= The Future of the Mind: The Scientific Quest to Understand, Enhance, and Empower the Mind, Hardcover, February 25, 2014, by Michio Kaku |accessdate=2014-11-26}}</ref>
In 2015 the book was translated into [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]<ref>{{cite book|last1=קאקו|first1=מיצ'יו|title=העתיד של המוח|date=2015|publisher=הוצאת אריה ניר|location=רמות השבים|language=Hebrew}}</ref>
==Overview== The book discusses various possibilities of advanced technology that can alter the brain and mind. Looking into things such as [[telepathy]], [[telekinesis]], [[consciousness]], [[artificial intelligence]], and [[transhumanism]], the book covers a wide range of topics. In it, Kaku proposes a "[[spacetime]] theory of consciousness". Similarly to [[Ray Kurzweil]], he believes the advances in silicon computing will serve our needs as opposed to producing a generation of robot overlords.<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/09/books/review/michio-kakus-future-of-the-mind.html?mcubz=0</ref>
==Reception== In March 16, 2014, ''The Future of the Mind'' made number one on [[The New York Times Bestseller|''The New York Times'' Bestseller]] list.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/2014-03-16/hardcover-nonfiction/list.html|publisher=[[nytimes.com]]|title=THE FUTURE OF THE MIND, by Michio Kaku. (Doubleday.)|accessdate=2014-11-26}}</ref>
